both vaccination and license this
year. More than 81 900 will be
sent to owners whose dogs have
rabies vaccinations valid for the
entire year of 1865. but whose
licenses, like all the rest of
Maricopa County s dogs, expire

The owner whose dog needs
both license and vaccination will
receive a two-ply IBM form when
he has the dog vaccinated either
by his veterinarian or at one of
the annual rabies vaccination
clinics.


This year S clinics are sched-
uled by location, on Saturdays and
Sundays from November 81
through December Is. The total
fee for each dog vaccinated and
licensed at the clinics will be
$500. This includes $500 for a
rabies vaccination good for three
years. and $500 for the 1865
dog license. Clinics are spon-
sored by the Central Arizona
Veterinary Medical Association
and the Maricopa County Health
Department.
